<task id="AIPU2-102" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Cross-pane: Playbook selection in Context specializes Chat agent</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>frontend, integration, cross-pane</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-074, AIPU2-086, AIPU2-079</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    When a user picks a playbook from the PlaybookGalleryWidget in the Context pane, the
    ConversationPane's SprkChat should immediately specialize to that playbook's agent
    (switching system prompt, tool set, and UI labels). Optionally the Workspace may clear
    or reconfigure its tabs based on the playbook's default widget configuration. This is the
    primary onboarding flow: Stage 1 (Landing) -> Stage 2 (Playbook Selected) lifecycle
    transition. Uses PaneEventBus (AIPU2-074), PlaybookGalleryWidget (AIPU2-086), and
    SprkChat (AIPU2-079).
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer responsible for pane lifecycle and playbook integration.</role>
  <goal>
    Selecting a playbook in PlaybookGalleryWidget dispatches a PlaybookSelectedEvent via
    PaneEventBus. ConversationPane receives it and calls SprkChat.setPlaybookId(playbookId),
    causing the chat to reload with the correct agent configuration. The Workspace pane
    updates its tab configuration based on the playbook's defaultWidgets list. The shell
    transitions from Stage 1 to Stage 2 lifecycle state.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/design.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ContextPane</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ConversationPane</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/SprkChat</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Define PlaybookSelectedEvent on PaneEventBus: { type: 'playbook-selected', playbookId: string, playbookName: string, defaultWidgets: WidgetConfig[] }.</step>
    <step>In PlaybookGalleryWidget (AIPU2-086), wire the playbook card click handler to dispatch PlaybookSelectedEvent via PaneEventBus with the full playbook config.</step>
    <step>In ConversationPane, subscribe to PlaybookSelectedEvent. On receipt, call SprkChat.setPlaybookId(playbookId) and update the pane header to show the playbook name.</step>
    <step>Implement SprkChat.setPlaybookId: close any active SSE stream, reset message history UI (keep persisted history), send a new session-init request with the selected playbookId to the backend, update system prompt label in the UI.</step>
    <step>In WorkspacePaneController, subscribe to PlaybookSelectedEvent. If defaultWidgets is non-empty, replace workspace tabs with the playbook's default widget set; if empty, retain current tabs.</step>
    <step>Trigger ThreePaneShell stage transition from Stage 1 (Landing) to Stage 2 (Playbook Selected) on PlaybookSelectedEvent receipt.</step>
    <step>Add a "Change playbook" affordance so the user can return to Stage 1 / playbook gallery.</step>
    <step>Test: from landing stage, select a playbook, verify chat reinitializes with correct agent, verify workspace tabs update, verify stage transitions to Stage 2.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Selecting a playbook card dispatches PlaybookSelectedEvent via PaneEventBus.</criterion>
    <criterion>SprkChat.setPlaybookId is called and the chat reinitializes with the correct playbook agent configuration.</criterion>
    <criterion>Workspace pane updates tabs to match the playbook's defaultWidgets configuration.</criterion>
    <criterion>ThreePaneShell transitions from Stage 1 (Landing) to Stage 2 (Playbook Selected).</criterion>
    <criterion>A "Change playbook" affordance is present and returns the user to Stage 1.</criterion>
    <criterion>No SSE stream race conditions: any active stream is closed before reinitializing.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
